<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 92-16-03 - Improved Engine Access Door Latch</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi921603" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>92-16-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>November, 1992</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>CAB</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Improved Engine Access Door Latch</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>3000
                    <daterange>
                        <enddate>04/04/1992</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to 3900 FC bus chassis built before April 4, 1992.</para>
                <para>An improvement to the engine cover has been made on the 3900 FC bus chassis. The improvement
                    consists of replacing the rubber plunger latch assembly with a slam latch design on the engine
                    access door. This improvement can be made on 3900 Series vehicles built prior to April 4, 1992,
                    using the parts and procedure described in this letter.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t9216031" frame="all">
                <title>Parts Information</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.01in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>2005709C91</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Engine Cover Access Door Latch Assembly</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>The engine cover access door latch assembly consists of:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>1 latch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>1 retainer</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>2 rivets</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>2 washers</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>1 stopper.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove engine cover from vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure and outline an opening in the engine cover for the engine cover access door
                    latch retainer as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9216031">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With a suitable cutting tool, cut out the opening for the retainer in the engine cover.
                    Cut the opening a little undersized then enlarge the opening by hand with a file to insure an
                    interference fit of the retainer to the opening.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The size of the opening is critical. Too large an opening will allow engine compartment air to
                        enter the vehicle.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the latch retainer in the opening. Use the retainer as a template and drill two
                    3/16 inch holes for rivets as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9216031">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rivets in the 3/16 inch holes to secure the latch retainer in the opening, put
                    the washers on the rivets, on the inside of the cover to reinforce the upset end of the rivet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the latch in the engine cover access door and replace it with the one supplied in
                    the new latch assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9216032">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, loosen the screw that secures the latch pawl (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9216031">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and adjust the pawl up or down so the access door is
                    level with the engine cover when closed. Tighten the pawl screw.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the stopper in hole in the engine cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9216031">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
